---
---

<section class="process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="process-header">
      <p class="eyebrow">— How I work</p>
      <h2>No retainers on day one. No guesswork.</h2>
      <p class="process-desc">
        Every engagement starts with a clear picture of what's actually going on.
        Most clients recoup the audit cost inside 60 days.
      </p>
    </div>

    <ol class="process-steps">
      <li class="step">
        <div class="step-number">01</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3>Stack Audit</h3>
          <p>
            I map everything your business runs on — tools, costs, workflows,
            integrations. Most audits surface 2–4 tools you're paying for but
            not using, and at least one process nobody owns.
          </p>
          <p class="step-output">Output: written report + debrief call · $1,000</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="step">
        <div class="step-number">02</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3>Fix What's Broken</h3>
          <p>
            If the audit reveals bigger structural problems — fragmented tools,
            missing workflows, a team that can't see what's happening — I build
            the replacement. One system your team actually uses.
          </p>
          <p class="step-output">Output: working infrastructure + runbooks · from $3,200</p>
        </div>
      </li>

      <li class="step">
        <div class="step-number">03</div>
        <div class="step-body">
          <h3>Ongoing Operator</h3>
          <p>
            For companies that want someone watching the stack permanently.
            I handle vendor renewals, onboard new tools, and respond when
            something breaks. You focus on the business.
          </p>
          <p class="step-output">Output: infrastructure under management · $1,100/month</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <p class="process-note">
      Not sure which fits? <a href="/contact">Tell me what's going on</a> and I'll tell you what makes sense.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .process {
    padding: var(--space-96) 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .process-header {
    max-width: 600px;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-64);
  }

  .process-header h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(24px, 3.5vw, 40px);
    font-weight: 900;
    color: var(--text);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin: var(--space-16) 0 var(--space-24);
    line-height: 1.15;
  }

  .process-desc {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }

  .process-steps {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .step {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-32);
    padding: var(--space-48) 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .step-number {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
    padding-top: 6px;
  }

  .step-body h3 {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-16);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .step-body p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 560px;
  }

  .step-output {
    margin-top: var(--space-16) !important;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px !important;
    color: var(--text-dim) !important;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .process-image {
    margin-top: var(--space-48);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    overflow: hidden;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .process-image img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 280px;
    object-fit: cover;
    display: block;
    filter: brightness(0.8);
  }

  .process-note {
    margin-top: var(--space-48);
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .process-note a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .process-note a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .step {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: var(--space-16);
    }
  }
</style>
